pan asian music festival elegant gathering i events at stanford pan asian music festival elegant gathering i facebook twitter email print add to calendar lectures and demonstrations associated with the eighth annual pan asian music festival take the format of elegant gatherings an ancient term used to describe a gathering of scholars and artists join masters yuan sha ji aeri and kazue sawai in an exploration of the history of asian instruments including the gu zheng koto and gayageum followed by a korean tea ceremony performed by experts in the tradition plus students from korea's inje university elegant gatherings also take place on 2 10 and 2 11 when friday february 3 2012 12 00 pm where campbell recital hall map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags arts performance music sponsor department of music admission free permalink http events stanford edu events 305 30545 more info last modified january 20 2012
